# Cleaning and beautifying Data
def printdashedline(i):
    [print("-", end="") for x in range(i)]
    print("\n")


def printmd(string):
    display(Markdown(string))
    

# Check if any NAs
print("Are there any NA values in dataset? : {}".format(heart_data.isnull().values.any()))
printdashedline(115)

# columns with NA Values
heart_data_NA_list = heart_data.columns[heart_data.isna().any()].tolist()
print("Which columns has NA values in dataset?\n {}".format(heart_data_NA_list))
printdashedline(115)

printmd("**What to do with NA data?**\n")

# percentage of NA values in columns
for hna in heart_data_NA_list:
    ratio = sum(heart_data[hna].isna())/heart_data.shape[0]
    print("Ratio of NA values to total values for column\t {} \tis : {p:3.4f}".format(hna, p=ratio))

# percentage of NA values in rows
heart_data_NA_rows = heart_data[heart_data.isnull().T.any().T]
print("\nTotal number of rows with NA values : {}".format(heart_data_NA_rows.shape[0]))
print("Ratio of NA rows with total data : {p:3.4f}".format(p=heart_data_NA_rows.shape[0]/heart_data.shape[0]))
printdashedline(115)


printmd("**Decision**\n")
print("We will drop NA rows because they are only ~14% of total dataset")
heart_df = heart_data.dropna()
print("Total rows left after drop : {}".format(heart_df.shape[0]))
print("Are there any NA values in refined dataframe ? : {}".format(heart_df.isnull().values.any()))
printdashedline(115)


# ranaming first column for better identification
heart_df.rename(columns={'male':'sex_male'},inplace=True)

# heart_df_st = heart_df[['age', 'currentSmoker', 'prevalentHyp','sysBP']]
# sns.pairplot(heart_df_st, size=2.5);

age_list = []
age_group = []
prevalentHyp_group = []
currentSmoker_group = []
chd_group = []

# grouping hypertension, smoking and TenyearCHD reading by age group
i = heart_df['age'].min()
while (i <= heart_df['age'].max()):
    age_list.append(i)
    age_group.append(heart_df[(heart_df['age'] >= i) & (heart_df['age'] < i+5)]['age'].count())
    prevalentHyp_group.append(heart_df[(heart_df['age'] >= i) & (heart_df['age'] < i+5) & (heart_df['prevalentHyp'] == 1)]['prevalentHyp'].count())
    currentSmoker_group.append(heart_df[(heart_df['age'] >= i) & (heart_df['age'] < i+5) & (heart_df['currentSmoker'] == 1)]['currentSmoker'].count())
    chd_group.append(heart_df[(heart_df['age'] >= i) & (heart_df['age'] < i+5) & (heart_df['TenYearCHD'] == 1)]['TenYearCHD'].count())
    i += 5

# creating overall ration from samples for better visualisation and avoid misconceptions due to lack of data
a=np.array(age_group, dtype=np.int)
b=np.array(prevalentHyp_group, dtype=np.int)
prevalentHyp_ratio = np.round(a/b,2)

b=np.array(currentSmoker_group, dtype=np.int)
currentSmoker_ratio = np.round(a/b,2)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,7))
plt.plot(age_list,prevalentHyp_ratio,label="Reported Hypertension (% age samples)")
plt.plot(age_list,currentSmoker_ratio,label="Active Smokers (% age samples)")
fig.suptitle('Hypertension and Active Smokers vs Age', fontsize=20)
plt.xlabel('Age', fontsize=18)
plt.ylabel('Ratio from reported samples', fontsize=18)
plt.legend(fontsize=16)
fig.savefig('hypertension_smoking.jpg')

Train and Test Split¶

Here we will use 2 techniques to compensate for imbalance in data (as highlighted in a graph above)

  1. Undersampling of train and test data - This method will make sure than we have equal samples of positive and Negative cases from actual data.
  2. Synthetic Sampling - This method creates synthetic positive cases so we have same number of training samples for modeling. It defers from point 1 in two ways: i) The actual samples are much more in case of synthetic sampling. ii) As the name suggests, synthetic sampling "generates" training data from existing samples. It doesn't represent actual samples.

Technique 1. Under Sampling¶

In [16]:
# Under Sampling Case

x_zeros = x[y==0]
x_ones = x[y==1]
y_zeros = y[y==0]
y_ones = y[y==1]

x_train_zeros,x_test_zeros,y_train_zeros,y_test_zeros = train_test_split(x_zeros,
                                                                         y_zeros,
                                                                         test_size=140,
                                                                         train_size=417,
                                                                         random_state=5)

x_train_ones,x_test_ones,y_train_ones,y_test_ones = train_test_split(x_ones,
                                                                     y_ones,
                                                                     test_size=140,
                                                                     train_size=417,
                                                                     random_state=5)

x_train = pd.concat([x_train_ones , x_train_zeros])
x_test = pd.concat([x_test_ones, x_test_zeros])
y_train = pd.concat([y_train_ones, y_train_zeros])
y_test = pd.concat([y_test_ones, y_test_zeros])

print(x_train.shape, x_test.shape)

# Feature Selection

feature_selector = SelectKBest(f_classif, k=8)
x_features = feature_selector.fit_transform(x_train, y_train)
feature_names = x_train.columns.values.tolist()

mask = feature_selector.get_support() #list of booleans
new_features = [] # The list of K best features

for bl, feature in zip(mask, feature_names):
    if bl:
        new_features.append(feature)

x_heart_df = pd.DataFrame(x_features, columns=new_features)

print(new_features)
print(x_heart_df.shape)
print(x_heart_df.describe())

Conclusion - Model Comparison¶

In [0]:
# Plot Final Results for all models

def model_res(model):
  acc = accuracy_score(y_test, model.predict(x_test))
  f1 = f1_score(y_test, model.predict(x_test))
  pre = precision_score(y_test, model.predict(x_test))
  rec = recall_score(y_test, model.predict(x_test))
  return [acc, f1, pre, rec]

measure_metrics = ['Accuracy','F1-Score','Precision','Recall']
In [44]:
_ = plt.figure(figsize=(12,7))
_ = plt.scatter(measure_metrics, model_res(logreg_model), c='b', 
            marker='D', label='Logistic Regression')
_ = plt.scatter(measure_metrics, model_res(rf_model), c='r', 
            marker='o', label='Random Forest')
_ = plt.scatter(measure_metrics, model_res(xgb_rscv), c='g', 
            marker='+', label='xgboost - Decision Trees')
_ = plt.scatter(measure_metrics, model_res(svmlin_rscv), c='k', 
            marker='^', label='Linear SVC')
_ = plt.ylim(0.4,1)
_ = plt.ylabel('Score', fontsize=18)
_ = plt.xlabel('Measurement Metrics', fontsize=18)
_ = plt.title('Model Comparison for Ten Year Heart Decision Prediction', fontsize=22)
_ = plt.legend(loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.5))
_ = plt.show()
